♪ now off we go ♪

02:14.499 --> 02:16.467
♪ oh, oh, oh ♪

02:16.534 --> 02:19.169
♪ now off we go ♪

02:22.924 --> 02:25.142
♪ sleep with the wind ♪

02:25.209 --> 02:27.928
♪ while it's still running
through your veins ♪

02:28.013 --> 02:30.080
♪ pass by faces ♪

02:30.148 --> 02:33.434
♪ and not recall
all the names now ♪

02:33.518 --> 02:36.219
My parents?
I'm so glad you asked.

02:36.271 --> 02:39.323
My parents are the two most
supportive people on the planet.

02:39.390 --> 02:40.574
Mm.

02:40.659 --> 02:43.327
If I could wrap my childhood
up in a bow

02:43.394 --> 02:44.745
and give it as a gift,
I would.

02:44.829 --> 02:46.247
What, with the mother
in prison

02:46.331 --> 02:47.781
and the absentee father?

02:47.866 --> 02:50.334
I just want it
to be perfect.

02:50.401 --> 02:51.502
I know,
but just try to relax.

02:51.569 --> 02:53.403
It's only
our first interview.

02:53.455 --> 02:54.955
And it could be our only.

02:55.040 --> 02:57.407
Do you know how crazy it is
that we got a call so soon?

02:57.459 --> 02:58.575
We need to prepare.

02:58.627 --> 03:00.594
We need to prepare
to be ourselves?

03:00.679 --> 03:03.464
Trust me. I have been
through this before.

03:03.548 --> 03:05.966
It takes some couples
years to adopt.

03:06.051 --> 03:09.920
You don't get an opportunity
like this every day.

03:09.971 --> 03:11.305
♪ As long
as we're leaving ♪

03:11.389 --> 03:13.807
It's like all the stars
aligned for us.

03:13.892 --> 03:17.194
You know, maybe we should
trust the stars, then.

03:17.261 --> 03:19.229
Just promise me that you'll
follow my lead today.

03:19.281 --> 03:21.282
Okay.

03:21.366 --> 03:22.816
Okay,
you're the expert.

03:22.901 --> 03:25.753
♪ All that we need ♪

03:25.820 --> 03:28.289
♪ open your eyes wide ♪

03:28.373 --> 03:30.374
All right, that's it.
Time's up.

03:30.442 --> 03:32.609
I can't believe
Ian just blew us off.

03:33.995 --> 03:35.663
Well, I guess
that the Kellerman apple

03:35.747 --> 03:37.280
doesn't fall far
from the douche-bag tree.

03:37.332 --> 03:40.217
I would've pulled this move,
too, back in the day.

03:40.284 --> 03:41.669
Yeah, and I wouldn't
have signed you.

03:41.753 --> 03:44.004
And you would've
regretted it.

03:44.089 --> 03:45.806
♪ And off we go ♪

03:45.890 --> 03:47.808
♪ oh, oh ♪

03:47.892 --> 03:50.761
♪ and off we go ♪

03:50.812 --> 03:52.629
♪ oh, oh ♪
Hey!

03:52.681 --> 03:54.798
♪ And off we go ♪

03:54.849 --> 03:57.067
Are you sure you're not gonna
regret me staying home today?

03:57.135 --> 03:58.986
W-why are you
wearing that?

03:59.070 --> 04:01.238
Because I'm so excited.
I've got a new sport to watch.

04:01.305 --> 04:03.140
I got new lingo to learn
and new plays to call

04:03.191 --> 04:05.142
and new cheers to cheer.

04:05.193 --> 04:08.145
Uh, uh, we want a catcher,
not a belly scratcher!

04:10.148 --> 04:11.949
There's no whistles
in baseball, mom.

04:12.000 --> 04:14.368
Oh. Well, there is now.

04:14.452 --> 04:15.703
Then the answer is no.

04:15.787 --> 04:17.671
I won't regret you
not being there.

04:17.755 --> 04:19.173
Oh, boo.
Get out of here, you.

04:24.346 --> 04:26.513
No whistles!

04:28.850 --> 04:31.018
Okay, here I come.

04:32.270 --> 04:33.604
Wow.

04:33.671 --> 04:35.839
Millicent Huxtable,
field reporter.

04:35.890 --> 04:37.474
I'd watch you
all day long.

04:37.525 --> 04:39.360
- Stop.
- I'm serious. You look great.

04:39.444 --> 04:40.527
Well, I feel bad.

04:40.612 --> 04:42.363
This job should be yours,
Marvin.

04:42.447 --> 04:43.814
You're great at your job,

04:43.865 --> 04:46.950
and I'm just some silly girl
pretending to be a reporter.

04:47.018 --> 04:48.619
Hey, they liked you
on the audition tape,

04:48.686 --> 04:51.205
and so did I,
and they were right.

04:51.289 --> 04:53.590
And the best part is now we'll be
able to afford a whole muffin --

04:53.658 --> 04:55.209
ooh, maybe even
those green pistachio ones.

04:55.293 --> 04:57.578
I love those, but they're --
so expensive.

04:57.662 --> 05:00.214
Do it for the green
pistachio muffins, Millie.

05:00.298 --> 05:02.399
Are you sure?

05:02.467 --> 05:04.752
I'm sure.
You're gonna do great.

05:04.836 --> 05:06.036
Thank you.

05:06.087 --> 05:08.872
Okay, here I go.

05:24.239 --> 05:25.439
I love you,
Marvin McFadden.

05:42.073 --> 05:44.625
Is that for brushing
or paddling?

05:44.709 --> 05:46.260
Very funny.

05:46.344 --> 05:47.628
It's for Haley.

05:47.712 --> 05:49.412
My mom had it engraved for me
when I was born,

05:49.464 --> 05:52.266
and since she's having a girl,
I thought she'd like it.

05:52.350 --> 05:54.351
You don't want to keep it?

05:54.418 --> 05:57.638
It'll mean a lot to her,
and she deserves it.

05:57.722 --> 06:00.357
Haley's such an incredible --

06:00.424 --> 06:02.726
Damn it!
She will not stop calling me.

06:02.777 --> 06:05.262
She's been stalking me
all morning to hang out,

06:05.313 --> 06:07.197
and I have to go to Brooke's and
help set up for her surprise shower,

06:07.265 --> 06:08.866
and I'm running
out of excuses.

06:08.933 --> 06:11.735
Easy. Tell her you have
to rotate your tires.

06:11.786 --> 06:14.037
No one ever wants to help
with tires.

06:14.105 --> 06:15.405
It's an inferior part
of the car.

06:17.659 --> 06:19.660
Hi, Haley.

06:19.744 --> 06:23.714
Oh, no, sorry. I had my phone
on silent by accident.

06:23.781 --> 06:28.502
Oh, I can't. I have to, uh,
rotate my tires.

06:28.586 --> 06:29.837
No, that's not a euphemism.

06:29.921 --> 06:32.256
Oh, really?

06:32.340 --> 06:34.308
Great. Yay.

06:34.392 --> 06:36.927
See you soon.

06:36.978 --> 06:39.563
Guess what Haley knows how to do
and offered to help me with

06:39.630 --> 06:41.298
right after we watch
"Love Actually"?

06:41.349 --> 06:43.967
Honestly, you haven't
rotated them in a while.

06:45.904 --> 06:47.271
That lying thing's
a tangled web.

06:49.140 --> 06:50.858
I was a great student --

06:50.942 --> 06:52.993
honor roll,
that sort of thing.

06:53.077 --> 06:55.996
And now we're homebodies.

06:56.080 --> 07:00.483
A cup of green tea and a movie
is us in a nutshell.

07:00.535 --> 07:02.586
Organic food.

07:02.653 --> 07:04.705
Love the organic food.

07:04.789 --> 07:07.674
Okay, uh,
that sounds nice.

07:07.759 --> 07:10.493
So, um, do you guys mind

07:10.545 --> 07:13.013
if I ask you what you do
for a living?

07:13.097 --> 07:15.299
Oh, well, actually --

07:15.350 --> 07:16.934
Ow.

07:17.001 --> 07:20.888
Actually, Julian is
a pretty big-time film director.

07:20.955 --> 07:22.940
He used to live
in Hollywood.

07:23.007 --> 07:25.275
And I am
a clothing designer.

07:25.343 --> 07:27.611
Do you know
Clothes Over Bros?

07:27.678 --> 07:30.447
Oh, no, I don't
really follow fashion.

07:30.514 --> 07:32.783
Oh. That's good.

07:32.850 --> 07:34.451
That's good.

07:34.518 --> 07:37.237
Okay, so, um,
what about your parents?

07:37.322 --> 07:40.207
Would there be some supportive
grandparents around?

07:40.291 --> 07:42.292
Define "supportive."

07:42.360 --> 07:45.528
Ow!
Dear. Honey.

07:45.580 --> 07:48.715
Our parents
are wonderful people --

07:48.800 --> 07:51.418
solid, even-keeled.

07:51.502 --> 07:53.020
Wouldn't you agree,
honey?

07:53.087 --> 07:56.173
Mm-hmm.

07:56.224 --> 07:58.308
♪ I can see our bodies... ♪

07:58.376 --> 08:00.677
That went better
than I expected.

08:00.728 --> 08:03.013
We sounded like
the perfect parents.

08:03.064 --> 08:04.932
We could've been
a little bit more ourselves,

08:05.016 --> 08:06.984
but I'm sure she loved us,
whoever we were in there.

08:07.051 --> 08:08.352
Trust me.

08:08.403 --> 08:09.770
I've been through
these kinds of things before,

08:09.854 --> 08:11.488
and that was
an a-plus interview.

08:11.555 --> 08:13.690
Yeah, I guess you're right.
How could she not love us?

08:13.741 --> 08:14.775
Look how adorable
we are.

08:16.560 --> 08:17.894
You know what I think?

08:17.946 --> 08:20.897
I think we might be getting
a baby, baby.

08:23.234 --> 08:24.618
Mm.

08:27.338 --> 08:29.840
♪ I don't want to be anything ♪

08:29.907 --> 08:33.510
♪ other than what I've been
trying to be lately ♪

08:33.577 --> 08:36.046
♪ all I have to do
is think of me ♪

08:36.097 --> 08:38.748
♪ and I have peace of mind ♪

08:38.799 --> 08:41.083
♪ I'm tired
of looking 'round rooms ♪

08:41.135 --> 08:42.769
♪ wondering what I gotta do ♪

08:42.854 --> 08:45.439
♪ or who I'm supposed to be ♪

