09:41.570 --> 09:44.655
Mm. I love you,
you know that?

09:44.723 --> 09:46.741
Nice to know,
since I love you back.

09:48.560 --> 09:51.228
So, what time's
the shower?

09:51.280 --> 09:54.081
Oh, whenever Quinn
gets Haley here.

09:54.166 --> 09:55.065
If.

09:55.117 --> 09:56.834
What do you mean, "if"?

09:56.902 --> 09:58.369
Surprise things
never work out.

09:58.420 --> 10:00.905
There's always stress
and telling people white lies

10:00.956 --> 10:03.291
by people who aren't even good
at telling white lies,

10:03.375 --> 10:04.575
and it's always a mess.

10:04.626 --> 10:06.594
Well, this one's
gonna be great.

10:06.678 --> 10:08.262
Okay.

10:09.915 --> 10:12.416
So, I was thinking
we -- oh.

10:12.467 --> 10:15.085
Are you
getting undressed?

10:15.137 --> 10:16.921
Yeah. Is that okay?

10:16.972 --> 10:19.724
Yeah. Go ahead.
I'll watch.

10:21.026 --> 10:24.395
Or we could try to break
the box spring.

10:24.446 --> 10:26.964
There isn't
a box spring.

10:27.032 --> 10:28.900
Even so,
get over here.

10:32.771 --> 10:34.288
Oh!

10:34.373 --> 10:36.574
Aah!

10:36.625 --> 10:37.775
You're right.
This <i>is</i> fun.

10:39.745 --> 10:42.613
We're getting a baby!

10:42.664 --> 10:44.549
Whoo!

10:44.616 --> 10:46.717
I'm gonna be a father!

10:49.054 --> 10:50.004
Hey, hey.

10:50.088 --> 10:51.839
Big day, coach Scott.
Yep.

10:51.924 --> 10:53.958
Your son is very excited
about Little League tryouts

10:54.009 --> 10:56.010
and surprisingly confident.

10:56.094 --> 10:57.645
He should be.
He's a Scott boy.

10:57.729 --> 11:00.014
What about the off-chance
that he doesn't do so well?

11:00.098 --> 11:01.766
You gonna go
all Dan Scott on him?

11:01.817 --> 11:05.152
I'm kidding! I just know
how competitive you are.

11:05.237 --> 11:06.320
I am not
that competitive.

11:07.689 --> 11:08.823
Okay. That's fair.

11:10.025 --> 11:11.642
Here.

11:12.995 --> 11:14.862
There's no whistles
in baseball, Hales.

11:14.947 --> 11:16.981
Yeah, so I've been told.

11:18.533 --> 11:20.701
♪ Someone said last night ♪

11:20.786 --> 11:21.869
Oh, and, Hales,

11:21.954 --> 11:23.337
my dad could never
really get over

11:23.422 --> 11:25.039
who he thought
he was supposed to be.

11:25.123 --> 11:27.325
But I'm just fine
with being Jamie Scott's dad

11:27.392 --> 11:28.876
and Haley James' husband

11:28.961 --> 11:30.494
and father to...

11:30.562 --> 11:32.046
To?

11:32.130 --> 11:33.931
...Little...

11:33.999 --> 11:34.849
Nice try.

11:34.933 --> 11:35.967
I gave it a shot.

11:36.018 --> 11:38.135
Actually, I-I do
have an idea,

11:38.186 --> 11:41.555
but I kind of want to run it
by somebody else first.

11:41.623 --> 11:42.640
Is that okay?

11:42.691 --> 11:44.892
Of course.

11:46.445 --> 11:47.511
Have fun!

11:47.562 --> 11:50.197
Go, team Scott!
Whoo-hoo!

11:58.540 --> 12:00.825
Hey, Haley's calling you.
Do you want me to get it?

12:00.876 --> 12:03.861
No, don't!
Don't answer it.

12:03.912 --> 12:04.462
Oh!

12:05.580 --> 12:07.415
Oh, she's driving me crazy.

12:07.499 --> 12:09.033
I need another excuse.
Think.

12:09.084 --> 12:10.418
Um, you could say --

12:10.502 --> 12:12.970
you're smothering me!

12:14.506 --> 12:16.040
Really?

12:16.091 --> 12:18.359
Yeah, I'm not --
not good at this.

12:18.427 --> 12:19.877
No.

12:19.928 --> 12:21.679
All right,
I'm headed out.

12:21.730 --> 12:24.381
I told Nathan and Clay
I'd help coach Little League.

12:24.433 --> 12:27.568
You're gonna help coach?

12:27.653 --> 12:29.153
Just because
my area of expertise is

12:29.220 --> 12:31.222
more in the butterfly-catching
aspect of the game

12:31.289 --> 12:32.773
does not mean
I will not be an asset.

12:32.841 --> 12:34.025
♪ I would do it ♪

12:34.076 --> 12:37.128
I'll give them a pep talk
during intermission.

12:37.195 --> 12:38.963
Intermission?

12:39.031 --> 12:40.081
Halftime?

12:40.165 --> 12:41.732
♪ Carrying the torch
for you ♪

12:41.783 --> 12:43.334
Seventh-inning stretch?

12:43.401 --> 12:45.219
There's only six innings
in Little League.

12:46.672 --> 12:48.039
Then I got nothing.

12:49.291 --> 12:52.426
Hi, Haley.

12:52.511 --> 12:54.628
Oh, sorry about that.

12:54.713 --> 12:56.747
No, no.

12:56.798 --> 12:59.183
Um, I'm actually already
on my way,

12:59.250 --> 13:01.752
so I'll just --
I'll see you soon.

13:01.803 --> 13:04.472
Yay!

13:04.556 --> 13:05.639
Ohh.

13:05.724 --> 13:07.692
Now I got nothing.

13:07.759 --> 13:10.111
I'm sorry. Can you
finish this by yourself?

13:10.195 --> 13:12.279
Yes, I'll be fine. Just make
sure she gets here on time.

13:12.364 --> 13:14.264
I will. Bye, Julian.

13:14.316 --> 13:16.600
♪ Someone said last night ♪

13:16.651 --> 13:17.952
Innings.

13:18.036 --> 13:18.903
You got it.

13:20.572 --> 13:23.607
♪ The voices in your head,
you got to ♪

13:23.658 --> 13:25.776
♪ keep it to yourself ♪

13:25.827 --> 13:27.444
♪ I know you're not talking
to me ♪

13:27.496 --> 13:29.797
♪ but it takes so long,
I don't want to be ♪

13:29.915 --> 13:31.298
You got it, Chuck.

13:31.383 --> 13:33.501
All right, come on, now.
Stay in front of it.

13:33.585 --> 13:36.804
Keep your eye on the ball.

13:36.888 --> 13:39.890
♪ I would do it
if you asked me to ♪

13:39.958 --> 13:42.143
♪ 'cause I'm still carrying
the torch for you ♪

13:42.227 --> 13:43.894
It took a bad hop!

13:43.962 --> 13:46.063
It's all right.
No, not the shoes.

13:46.131 --> 13:49.433
You guys suck!

13:55.741 --> 13:56.574
Jamie.

13:59.444 --> 14:00.611
A little late.

14:00.662 --> 14:02.913
Uh, sorry, man.
I had this, uh, thing.

14:02.981 --> 14:05.649
Do me a favor
and get her name.

14:05.700 --> 14:07.451
Hey. I'm Clay.

14:07.502 --> 14:09.086
You must be...
Kate.

14:10.922 --> 14:11.839
Hey, Kate.

14:11.923 --> 14:14.091
Yeah, Kate here
loves baseball.

14:14.159 --> 14:15.042
Players.

14:15.127 --> 14:16.827
Yeah.

14:16.878 --> 14:18.662
Ian, I want you to meet my son.
Jamie, this is Ian Kellerman.

14:18.713 --> 14:21.132
He's gonna be the next big thing
in the major leagues

14:21.183 --> 14:22.166
if we have anything
to say about it.

14:22.217 --> 14:23.184
What's up, little man?

14:23.268 --> 14:24.051
Hey.

14:24.136 --> 14:25.803
Dude, nice glove.

14:25.854 --> 14:28.338
That glove belonged
to Roberto Clemente!

14:29.340 --> 14:32.109
Ooh, butterfly.

14:32.177 --> 14:34.178
So, you got tryouts
today, huh?

14:34.229 --> 14:35.312
Want to know a secret?

14:35.363 --> 14:37.398
Sure.
All right.

14:37.482 --> 14:39.016
When you're getting
up to bat,

14:39.067 --> 14:41.452
really take your time getting
into the batter's box, right?

14:41.519 --> 14:42.620
And then right before
the first pitch,

14:42.687 --> 14:44.538
make eye contact
with the pitcher.

14:44.623 --> 14:46.207
Stare him down.

14:46.291 --> 14:48.125
Like this?

14:48.193 --> 14:49.860
Ooh, that's strong.
Good.

14:49.911 --> 14:52.913
Then, right at the last second,
smile at him.

14:52.998 --> 14:54.081
Really freaks
them out.

14:54.166 --> 14:56.584
Sweet. Thanks.
No problem, man.

14:56.701 --> 14:58.636
All right, guys,
I got to run.

14:58.703 --> 15:00.037
I got to get Kate here home.

15:01.006 --> 15:01.972
Hey, uh,
thanks for that, man.

15:02.040 --> 15:03.808
Let's get together later,

15:03.875 --> 15:05.375
say, uh, 3:00?

15:05.427 --> 15:06.560
Sure.

15:06.645 --> 15:08.095
Let's go, Kate.

15:08.180 --> 15:10.815
Ian.

15:10.882 --> 15:12.216
3:00 means 3:00.

15:12.267 --> 15:13.767
Hey, I said I was sorry,
all right?

15:13.852 --> 15:15.603
All right.

15:16.905 --> 15:19.190
All right.

15:19.241 --> 15:20.858
Let's get
this audition started.

15:20.909 --> 15:22.776
Julian, there's no whistles
in baseball.

15:22.861 --> 15:23.911
Or auditions.

15:26.281 --> 15:28.332
Oh, Brooke invited us over
later, so I told her

15:28.399 --> 15:30.367
we'd have second half
of girl's day over there.

15:30.418 --> 15:31.902
I hope that's okay.

15:31.953 --> 15:34.071
Nah.
I don't think so.

15:34.122 --> 15:35.873
W-what?

15:35.924 --> 15:37.174
Well, I -- sorry.

15:37.242 --> 15:39.376
I just haven't had the house
to myself in so long.

15:39.427 --> 15:42.046
I kind of was looking forward
to sitting on the couch

15:42.097 --> 15:44.915
and doing nothing all day,
except for rotating those tires.

15:46.601 --> 15:49.803
Great.

15:49.888 --> 15:55.526
Actually, there is a reason
I invited you over.

15:55.593 --> 15:58.028
Okay, fine,
I will French-braid your hair,

15:58.096 --> 15:59.980
but you've got to learn
to do this yourself.

16:00.065 --> 16:01.532
You're having a daughter,
you know.

16:01.599 --> 16:06.987
A daughter that I really want
to name after mom.

16:09.741 --> 16:10.958
I remember you told me once

16:11.042 --> 16:12.960
that you wanted to name
your first daughter Lydia,

16:13.044 --> 16:15.112
so I just wanted to check
if that was okay with you.

16:15.163 --> 16:16.630
You know what I want?

16:16.715 --> 16:18.549
I want a niece
named Lydia.

16:20.952 --> 16:23.620
And she's gonna be beautiful,
just like her mom.

16:25.757 --> 16:27.457
And just like our mom.

16:45.131 --> 16:47.986
You guys better move
10 feet back out there.

16:48.111 --> 16:49.779
♪ Why would I make that face? ♪

16:49.830 --> 16:52.281
You're about to get
the Chuck special.

16:52.332 --> 16:54.700
♪ Why would I test my faith? ♪

16:54.785 --> 16:56.318
♪ oh, why would I? ♪

16:56.370 --> 16:58.871
♪ oh, whoa ♪

16:58.956 --> 17:01.541
♪ I see that rain cloud
coming right for me ♪

17:01.625 --> 17:03.759
Man, I got hosed!

17:03.827 --> 17:06.295
Jamie Scott, you're up.

17:06.346 --> 17:08.297
Next time, just point
to the dugout.

17:08.348 --> 17:09.682
♪ Why would I ♪

17:09.766 --> 17:12.334
♪ when I'm so far away? ♪

17:12.386 --> 17:14.887
♪ oh, why would I? ♪

17:14.972 --> 17:16.388
♪ oh, whoa ♪

17:16.473 --> 17:19.559
♪ I guess I've always been
a bit of a fighter ♪

17:28.351 --> 17:31.787
♪ from now on, wear my love
for you loose ♪

17:31.855 --> 17:34.290
No fair. Coach's son!

17:34.357 --> 17:37.293
♪ I am just passing through ♪

17:37.360 --> 17:41.380
♪ from now on,
just my feeling is true ♪

17:41.465 --> 17:43.132
Hi.
Hi.

17:43.199 --> 17:44.550
♪ Call me royal blue ♪

17:44.635 --> 17:46.168
Can you believe
all this?

17:46.220 --> 17:48.704
Well, yeah, sort of.

17:48.755 --> 17:50.756
I did used to have
that job.

17:50.841 --> 17:52.475
I didn't know I had
to write my own stories.

17:52.542 --> 17:54.043
I don't know how
to write my own stories.

17:54.094 --> 17:55.127
I'm sorry.
I should've told you that.

17:55.195 --> 17:56.512
I should go.

17:56.563 --> 17:59.715
I have to get
to Haley's baby shower.

18:00.934 --> 18:02.985
What's so funny?

18:03.053 --> 18:05.137
Um, you might want to leave
that stuff here,

18:05.205 --> 18:07.406
unless you're planning on doing
a story about the shower.

18:07.491 --> 18:09.992
Sorry.

18:10.060 --> 18:11.160
See you.

18:11.227 --> 18:15.865
♪ Looking for a way out ♪

18:15.916 --> 18:19.619
♪ from now on,
with the sky as my roof ♪

18:20.871 --> 18:22.204
All right.

18:22.256 --> 18:23.923
In no order of importance,
talent, or favoritism,

18:24.007 --> 18:26.342
we have Madison.

18:27.628 --> 18:30.746
You see that?
Fortitude.

18:30.797 --> 18:31.964
Strong.

18:32.049 --> 18:34.467
Okay, Steven.

18:34.551 --> 18:36.269
All right, Steven.

18:36.353 --> 18:38.087
Next is Daniel.

18:38.138 --> 18:39.305
Daniel.

18:39.389 --> 18:41.107
Daniel.

18:41.191 --> 18:42.475
Clyde.

18:43.944 --> 18:45.094
Uh, Jamie Scott.

18:50.367 --> 18:51.317
Uh, Chuck.

18:51.401 --> 18:53.202
Mvp!

18:53.269 --> 18:54.436
Mvp Chuck!

18:54.488 --> 18:56.405
Oh!

18:56.456 --> 18:58.958
♪ Ohh ♪

18:59.042 --> 19:03.996
♪ from now on,
fly as high as I want ♪

19:04.081 --> 19:05.831
♪ from now on,
I'll show my weak spot ♪

19:05.916 --> 19:07.466
What's this?

19:07.551 --> 19:09.001
Ice-cream party
for Jamie.

19:09.086 --> 19:10.336
Uh, no,
we have to get going

19:10.420 --> 19:12.421
because Brooke's
expecting us, remember?

19:12.472 --> 19:13.639
Oh, Brooke can wait.

19:13.724 --> 19:16.142
Ice cream is the best part
about Little League.

19:16.226 --> 19:18.127
♪ Whoa ♪

19:20.130 --> 19:23.933
♪ Whoa ♪

19:23.984 --> 19:27.803
♪ whoa ♪

19:27.854 --> 19:30.656
Mmm.

19:30.741 --> 19:33.442
Eating ice cream is the best
part about Little League,

19:33.493 --> 19:35.411
except for maybe
catching butterflies.

19:36.697 --> 19:38.030
Mmm.

19:38.115 --> 19:40.149
Okay, I'm supposed to get Haley
to her shower,

19:40.200 --> 19:41.250
so please help me out.

19:41.317 --> 19:44.203
Hey!
Who wants sprinkles?

19:44.287 --> 19:46.088
Sprinkles are good.
Yeah, and whipped cream.

19:46.156 --> 19:47.790
Please. Thank you.
Okay.

19:47.841 --> 19:49.458
Quinny, I made some ice cream
for us, too.

19:49.509 --> 19:50.826
Oh, yay.

19:53.680 --> 19:55.715
Eat. Eat your ice cream.

19:57.718 --> 19:58.768
Eat. Let's go.

20:02.055 --> 20:03.022
Go.

20:04.191 --> 20:07.176
Okay, mmm. I'm done.
We can go.

20:07.227 --> 20:09.278
Quinn, there's no rush.

20:09.345 --> 20:11.030
- We got to leave and go to Brooke's.
- Why?

20:11.114 --> 20:12.865
Because we're throwing you
a surprise shower today!

20:12.949 --> 20:14.734
Ow. Brain freeze.

20:14.818 --> 20:17.286
You guys are throwing me
a baby shower?

20:17.353 --> 20:19.521
Yeah.

20:19.573 --> 20:20.856
Please act surprised.

20:26.046 --> 20:27.797
Surprise! Surprise!
Surprise! Surprise!

20:27.864 --> 20:31.584
Oh, my gosh. What do
you guys mean, surprise?

20:31.668 --> 20:33.886
It's not like it's
my birthday or anything.

20:33.970 --> 20:34.970
That too much?

20:35.038 --> 20:36.922
Yes.
Hi!

20:39.042 --> 20:41.060
You told her,
didn't you?

20:41.144 --> 20:42.211
Totally.

20:43.713 --> 20:46.348
Oh, yay!

20:51.153 --> 20:52.887
So, tell me again
who this kid is.

20:52.979 --> 20:54.896
Oh, he's a douche.

20:54.981 --> 20:56.281
He's a potential client.

20:56.348 --> 20:57.566
He's a douche-y one.

20:57.650 --> 20:59.618
Yeah.
Well, this is it.

20:59.685 --> 21:01.069
We're meeting him
on a boat?

21:01.154 --> 21:02.654
Sweet.

21:02.705 --> 21:04.956
Now I can say "I'm on a boat"
when I'm actually on a boat.

21:05.024 --> 21:06.691
Hope you brought
your flippy-floppys.

21:06.743 --> 21:08.359
♪ Lay down your spade ♪

21:08.411 --> 21:10.662
Uh, how do we knock?

21:10.713 --> 21:12.264
Maybe just rock it a bit?

21:12.331 --> 21:13.582
Too late.

21:13.666 --> 21:20.138
♪ Rather watch
the colors fade a while ♪

21:20.206 --> 21:24.009
♪ from pawnshop shades
to balconies ♪

21:24.060 --> 21:26.144
Take care, Tracy.

21:26.212 --> 21:28.546
Her name's Tracy.

21:28.598 --> 21:30.381
So, you live on a boat?

21:30.433 --> 21:32.584
No, I party on a boat.

21:32.652 --> 21:34.186
It's my dad's pride and joy,

21:34.253 --> 21:35.987
so I like to trash it
now and then.

21:36.055 --> 21:37.155
You guys in?

21:37.223 --> 21:39.724
Maybe we should just go
to a bar.

21:39.792 --> 21:41.226
♪ Still be coming in ♪

21:43.780 --> 21:45.614
Okay, one more thing.

21:45.698 --> 21:46.915
Ooh.

21:46.999 --> 21:49.084
Oh, my goodness.

21:49.168 --> 21:51.069
I am the queen.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

21:51.120 --> 21:53.288
Okay, is this from your
bachelorette party?

21:53.372 --> 21:55.257
Reuse, recycle.

21:59.578 --> 22:01.463
So, when's your big party coming?
For what?

22:01.547 --> 22:03.765
Oh, shut up. You know you're
totally getting a ring soon.

22:03.850 --> 22:04.966
You lucky bitch.

22:05.051 --> 22:07.719
No, no, no,
I'm not getting a ring.

22:07.770 --> 22:09.805
Are you and Clay
getting engaged?

22:09.889 --> 22:11.690
I need to hear stories. I'm having
postpartum wedding blues.

22:11.757 --> 22:13.441
Please tell me everything.

22:14.593 --> 22:17.145
All right, let's get this shower
officially started.

22:17.230 --> 22:19.430
These presents aren't gonna
open up themselves.

22:19.482 --> 22:20.816
Nice dodge, ring-getter.

22:22.285 --> 22:24.286
That was nice.
Finally.

22:26.539 --> 22:28.657
So, Ian, how come your dad
hates Nathan?

22:28.741 --> 22:31.276
What he means is he and I
got off on the wrong foot

22:31.327 --> 22:32.961
and never really got back
on the right one.

22:33.045 --> 22:36.665
♪ The boys around here
don't respect a thing at all ♪

22:36.749 --> 22:38.049
That's funny.

22:38.117 --> 22:40.886
Had a similar experience
with the old man.

22:40.953 --> 22:42.287
Well, maybe you
can fix it.

22:42.338 --> 22:43.755
You know, there was a time
when I barely spoke to my dad,

22:43.806 --> 22:44.673
but it's good now.

22:44.757 --> 22:46.224
It's not gonna happen,
dude.

22:46.292 --> 22:48.143
My dad cares
about three things --

22:48.227 --> 22:50.962
books, his dog,
and that boat.

22:51.013 --> 22:52.731
Well, you have to admit,
the dog <i>is</i> pretty cool.

22:54.100 --> 22:55.600
He rides skateboards.

22:55.651 --> 22:56.985
A skateboarding dog?

22:57.053 --> 22:58.803
That's pretty cool.

22:58.855 --> 23:01.406
What about your mom, Ian?
Are you close to her?

23:01.473 --> 23:04.159
Well, I was,
but my mom was a smart woman.

23:04.243 --> 23:06.111
She had the good sense
to divorce my dad and die

23:06.162 --> 23:07.696
before he could make her
anymore miserable.

23:10.366 --> 23:12.417
Are you guys sure you don't want
to go back and trash the boat?

23:21.093 --> 23:23.411
So, even though we come
from a big family,

23:23.479 --> 23:25.463
Haley and I
have always been close.

23:25.514 --> 23:28.300
You know, you've always been
there for me, my little sis --

23:28.351 --> 23:30.402
someone to believe in,

23:30.469 --> 23:32.354
someone to share
all my secrets with,

23:32.438 --> 23:36.191
and now...

23:36.275 --> 23:37.893
Jamie's getting
a little sister,

23:37.977 --> 23:41.613
and I know that he's gonna
love her as much as I love you.

23:41.680 --> 23:43.448
And you're gonna love
your daughter

23:43.515 --> 23:44.649
as much as mom loved us.

23:52.959 --> 23:54.793
Quinn.

23:57.463 --> 23:59.881
This is yours.
Mom gave it to you.

23:59.966 --> 24:02.217
I know, but now
I'm giving it to you.

24:05.671 --> 24:06.922
"My girl."

24:08.307 --> 24:10.141
Thank you, sis.

24:10.209 --> 24:11.977
You're welcome.

24:12.044 --> 24:14.212
I love you.

24:14.263 --> 24:15.230
Oh.

24:18.935 --> 24:20.986
So, you guys
have any brothers?

24:21.053 --> 24:22.320
Mnh-mnh.

24:22.388 --> 24:25.824
I have a...
Yes. Yeah.

24:25.891 --> 24:28.059
So you guys
understand, then.

24:28.110 --> 24:29.411
It was
just me growing up,

24:29.495 --> 24:30.829
so all my dad's hopes and dreams
were pinned on me.

24:30.896 --> 24:32.580
I might have had
a brother,

24:32.665 --> 24:34.749
but that didn't save either of us
from our dad's failed dreams.

24:34.834 --> 24:36.451
So you get it.

24:36.535 --> 24:38.169
I get it.
Oh, he gets it.

24:38.237 --> 24:39.921
Trust me.

24:40.006 --> 24:41.423
I'll be right back.

24:41.507 --> 24:46.077
♪ Oh, you won't hide,
I, I, I, I, I ♪

24:46.128 --> 24:47.929
Dude, you have been zen
all day today.

24:47.997 --> 24:50.098
What's going on with you?

24:50.182 --> 24:51.916
Just taking in
all the dad talk

24:51.968 --> 24:54.269
because Brooke and I
are going to adopt.

24:54.337 --> 24:56.354
Yeah, we had
our first interview

24:56.422 --> 24:58.523
with a birth mother
this morning,

24:58.590 --> 25:00.642
and it went great,
so we'll see.

25:00.726 --> 25:03.028
That is news
worth celebrating.

25:03.095 --> 25:05.647
♪ ...Rise, Sherry, rise ♪

25:05.731 --> 25:08.616
Ooh, thank you...
Mm-hmm.

25:08.701 --> 25:11.403
...For the champagne <i>and</i>
<i>for possibly saving my life.</i>

25:11.454 --> 25:13.104
Well, I'll drink
to that.

25:13.155 --> 25:14.122
Cheers.

25:14.206 --> 25:16.107
♪ Wondering why ♪

25:16.158 --> 25:17.125
♪ "no one told ya!" ♪

25:17.209 --> 25:18.827
Oh, I miss beer.

25:18.911 --> 25:20.829
Get someone to drink it
for you.

25:20.913 --> 25:22.764
The buzz isn't as good,
but the hangover's better.

25:22.832 --> 25:25.250
Okay,
chug that beer for me.

25:25.301 --> 25:27.552
No, have -- have Brooke do it.
She's the expert.

25:27.619 --> 25:29.120
What?!
Come on. Oh, Brooke!

25:29.171 --> 25:30.805
Yeah, Brooke,
chug a beer for me.

25:30.890 --> 25:32.290
No way.
Come on.

25:32.341 --> 25:34.292
It'll be like
a designated driver,

25:34.343 --> 25:36.627
but a designated drinker --
please?

25:36.679 --> 25:38.480
Listen to
the pregnant lady.

25:38.564 --> 25:40.265
I <i>so</i> should not have
saved you.

25:40.316 --> 25:42.067
All right.
All right.

25:43.903 --> 25:46.187
Oh, that looks
so refreshing.

25:46.272 --> 25:47.906
Okay.

26:03.172 --> 26:06.091
Whoo! Whoo!
Whoo! Whoo!

26:17.623 --> 26:19.623
I'm so sorry...

26:19.630 --> 26:22.465
I-I didn't know that you
were stopping by today.

26:22.837 --> 26:25.005
It's totally okay,
of course.

26:25.056 --> 26:27.224
We're just throwing
a baby shower for my friend.

26:27.309 --> 26:29.209
Okay. It's okay.
I understand.

26:29.261 --> 26:31.478
Um, I-I just came by
to bring you these --

26:31.546 --> 26:33.880
a little thank-you
for meeting me this morning.

26:33.932 --> 26:36.150
I know it was last-minute.

26:36.217 --> 26:39.320
You didn't have
to do that.

26:39.387 --> 26:41.939
Do you want to come in
and stay a while?

26:42.023 --> 26:45.576
Julian's not here, but you can
meet some of our friends.

26:45.660 --> 26:47.661
No, I-I should go.
I don't want to crash.

26:47.729 --> 26:50.397
No, honestly, stay.
I'd love it.

26:52.200 --> 26:55.786
Um, just one thing --
I hope this isn't weird.

26:55.870 --> 26:58.405
We haven't told anyone
about this,

26:58.456 --> 27:00.541
that we're trying
to adopt.

27:00.592 --> 27:03.260
I just didn't want to get
my hopes up

27:03.345 --> 27:06.079
in case
it didn't happen, so...

27:06.131 --> 27:07.014
Hi.

27:08.249 --> 27:09.550
Hi.

27:09.601 --> 27:11.552
Haley, uh, this is, um --
this is --

27:11.603 --> 27:13.387
I-I'm -- I'm Chloe.

27:13.455 --> 27:15.139
I-I came by
to bring you guys

27:15.206 --> 27:17.241
some cookies
for your baby shower.

27:17.309 --> 27:18.925
Thank you.
That's really sweet of you.

27:18.977 --> 27:20.160
Everybody treats you so nice
when you're pregnant.

27:20.228 --> 27:22.429
How far along are you?

27:22.480 --> 27:25.366
Um, about to pop,
far along.

27:25.433 --> 27:28.035
You must be starving.
Feel free to have some food.

27:28.102 --> 27:30.937
And just, you know,
don't eat my ho ho cake.

27:32.374 --> 27:35.225
Um, Millie, will you show
Chloe around?

27:35.293 --> 27:37.745
She's a fashion student
and a friend.

27:37.796 --> 27:40.297
Okay.
Okay?

27:40.382 --> 27:41.665
Haley.

27:41.750 --> 27:45.252
♪ Everything will be
all right ♪

27:45.303 --> 27:47.671
♪ everything will be
all right ♪

27:47.756 --> 27:48.806
♪ whoo ♪

27:48.890 --> 27:50.257
I need
to tell you something.

27:50.308 --> 27:51.258
Do you have
any pickles?

27:51.309 --> 27:52.926
Haley!
What?

27:52.978 --> 27:55.262
Julian and I only met Chloe
this morning.

27:55.313 --> 27:57.014
She's putting her baby up
for adoption,

27:57.098 --> 27:59.316
and she met with us.

27:59.401 --> 28:00.818
Oh, my --
shh!

28:00.902 --> 28:02.853
Nobody knows yet.

28:02.937 --> 28:06.139
Oh, sorry.

28:06.191 --> 28:07.574
Oh, my God,
I can't keep this in.

28:07.642 --> 28:09.476
We might be moms together.

28:09.527 --> 28:12.413
But it's only if she likes us,
and it's just the interview phase.

28:12.480 --> 28:13.831
How could she
not like you?

28:13.915 --> 28:16.083
Really? Do you think so?
Are you kidding me?

28:16.150 --> 28:17.785
There's no way that girl
can spend any time with you

28:17.836 --> 28:19.986
and not think you would be
an amazing mother.

28:20.038 --> 28:22.539
My God!

28:22.624 --> 28:23.674
So, how does it work?

28:23.758 --> 28:24.958
Does he just guess
what you like,

28:25.010 --> 28:26.343
or do you guys
talk about it beforehand?

28:26.428 --> 28:27.711
I mean,
that seems less fun,

28:27.829 --> 28:29.046
but then you at least get
the ring that you want.

28:29.130 --> 28:30.431
Oh, are you
getting engaged?

28:30.498 --> 28:32.850
No, I'm just dating.

28:32.934 --> 28:34.184
They're in limbo.

28:34.269 --> 28:35.436
They're more than dating
but not yet engaged.

28:35.503 --> 28:37.554
I am, too -- limbo.

28:37.639 --> 28:39.523
No, we're not in limbo.

28:39.607 --> 28:41.392
I just don't feel the need
to rush into anything.

28:41.476 --> 28:42.993
I mean, maybe if
I got pregnant, but...

28:43.061 --> 28:46.947
♪ All right ♪

28:47.014 --> 28:48.982
I can't imagine
having kids, man,

28:49.034 --> 28:50.868
until I'm like 40,
maybe.

28:50.952 --> 28:52.653
Kids are great.
You'll see.

28:52.704 --> 28:55.155
And hopefully Julian
will be seeing very soon.

28:55.206 --> 28:58.358
Well, dude, if it does happen,
don't be a dick.

28:58.410 --> 28:59.743
Okay.

28:59.828 --> 29:02.546
I'm just saying, like, don't try
to make your kid be you.

29:02.630 --> 29:06.917
My dad
never got me, ever,

29:07.001 --> 29:10.704
not when I was 5,
not now.

29:10.755 --> 29:13.307
You ever try talking
to him about it?

29:13.374 --> 29:15.375
No, man.

29:15.427 --> 29:16.877
I stopped trying
to talk to him

29:16.928 --> 29:18.645
right about the time
he stopped caring

29:18.713 --> 29:19.897
if we
ever really spoke.

29:19.981 --> 29:23.600
♪ Ohh ♪

29:23.685 --> 29:25.486
Hi.
Here you go.

29:25.553 --> 29:26.854
Oh, thank you.

29:26.905 --> 29:28.405
Brooke, I was just telling Chloe
about my new job.

29:28.490 --> 29:29.890
Oh, I forgot
to congratulate you.

29:29.941 --> 29:31.391
Don't worry about it.

29:31.443 --> 29:33.110
At this rate, I could join you
in the unemployment line

29:33.194 --> 29:35.395
by the end
of the week.

29:35.447 --> 29:38.231
Oh.
I'm not unemployed.

29:38.283 --> 29:41.034
Okay, to-ma-to, to-mah-to.
You lost your company.

29:41.086 --> 29:42.336
Um...
So, anyway, about my new job,

29:42.403 --> 29:45.389
they gave me
so much work to do,

29:45.457 --> 29:48.709
I'd have to start doing coke
again just to get it all done.

29:48.760 --> 29:50.294
I'm joking.
She's joking.

29:50.378 --> 29:51.628
I can joke
about rehab now.

29:51.713 --> 29:52.713
Good.

29:52.764 --> 29:54.264
Wait.
You're unemployed?

29:54.349 --> 29:56.216
I thought you said you designed clothes.
I do.

29:56.267 --> 29:59.186
Well, I had
a clothing company,

29:59.253 --> 30:01.105
a very successful one.

30:01.189 --> 30:05.476
We just got into some trouble,
so I don't have that anymore.

30:05.560 --> 30:08.261
But I'm figuring out
what I'm gonna do next

30:08.313 --> 30:10.764
with all my --
what?

30:10.815 --> 30:13.534
Really?
Who's that?

30:13.601 --> 30:14.902
Brooke, your bitch
of a mom's here.

30:14.953 --> 30:16.937
Mother.

30:16.988 --> 30:19.156
Why don't you
return my calls?

30:19.240 --> 30:20.374
This is really not
a good time.

30:20.441 --> 30:21.492
I thought we were good
after the wedding.

30:21.576 --> 30:22.576
Apparently
someone goes to prison

30:22.627 --> 30:24.044
and you don't
cut them a break?

30:24.111 --> 30:25.162
Wait. Prison?

30:25.246 --> 30:27.214
Yeah, prison.
Get used to it, everyone.

30:27.281 --> 30:30.450
I went to prison. It's not
that big a deal. It happens.

30:30.502 --> 30:33.119
Victoria, have a Martini
and calm down.

30:33.171 --> 30:35.455
Nobody here is ashamed
about jail time.

30:35.507 --> 30:38.008
I mean, I went to jail,
and I am not ashamed to say it.

30:38.092 --> 30:40.293
Honestly, who hasn't
been to jail?

30:40.345 --> 30:41.678
I remember my visit
very fondly.

30:41.763 --> 30:44.631
Okay, can we all stop
saying "jail"?

30:44.682 --> 30:46.016
Haley?
Yeah.

30:46.100 --> 30:48.301
Let's just be rational
and stop overexaggerating.

30:48.353 --> 30:49.736
Jail is so not
that big of a deal.

30:49.804 --> 30:50.938
Well, you would know.

30:50.989 --> 30:52.639
I mean, you've been
more than any of us.

30:52.690 --> 30:54.608
Okay, wait.
You've <i>all</i> been to jail?

30:54.659 --> 30:55.642
Ooh, no.
I haven't.

30:55.693 --> 30:56.693
She hasn't been.

30:56.778 --> 30:57.778
Yet.

30:57.829 --> 30:59.196
I haven't yet.
Thank you.

30:59.280 --> 31:01.081
Okay, you know what? I'm gonna go.
No, it's --

31:01.148 --> 31:03.000
I wanted to make a toast

31:03.117 --> 31:06.820
to my amazing friend Brooke
for throwing this party

31:06.871 --> 31:12.092
and for...saving
my son's life,

31:12.159 --> 31:16.329
because if she hadn't
risked hers to save Jamie,

31:16.381 --> 31:20.551
I would not be standing here,
with all of you, happy.

31:20.635 --> 31:21.635
♪ Haunted by the same dream ♪

31:21.686 --> 31:23.020
Brooke, there is a reason

31:23.104 --> 31:25.338
why you are Jamie's godmother.

31:25.390 --> 31:27.858
And I'm thankful every day
that you are.

31:29.978 --> 31:31.228
♪ Feels like a rain cloud ♪

31:31.312 --> 31:34.615
So, here's to my best friend,
Brooke Davis.

31:34.682 --> 31:39.870
There is no one else to whom
I would trust my child more.

31:39.954 --> 31:42.739
♪ Eyes making rainbows ♪

31:42.824 --> 31:46.460
♪ as the rain comes down ♪

31:48.997 --> 31:53.000
♪ you know what I think
we should do ♪

31:53.051 --> 31:54.051
♪ take a train ♪

31:54.135 --> 31:55.919
You almost forgot this.

31:56.004 --> 31:58.171
Thanks.

31:58.223 --> 32:00.841
Chloe, wait.

32:00.892 --> 32:02.392
There's something
I need to say to you

32:02.460 --> 32:03.727
before you decide

32:03.811 --> 32:06.063
that we're not the right parents
for your baby,

32:06.147 --> 32:08.098
starting with I'm sorry.

32:08.182 --> 32:12.319
I know I said a bunch of things
to you this morning

32:12.386 --> 32:13.737
that weren't true,

32:13.821 --> 32:16.857
and I left out some things
that maybe I shouldn't have,

32:16.908 --> 32:19.443
like losing my company

32:19.527 --> 32:23.747
and maybe
my mom going to prison.

32:23.815 --> 32:25.699
But I did that
because I was worried

32:25.750 --> 32:27.117
about what you would think
of us.

32:27.201 --> 32:30.621
Brooke,
I'm 19 and pregnant.

32:30.705 --> 32:33.540
I kind of get the whole
passing-judgment thing.

32:33.591 --> 32:35.092
But I'm not 19,

32:35.176 --> 32:37.511
and I know that I should've
been honest with you.

32:37.578 --> 32:40.380
So be honest now.

32:43.301 --> 32:47.587
When I was a teenager,
I was a mess.

32:47.639 --> 32:52.276
♪ Standing on the edge
of nothing ♪

32:52.360 --> 32:54.478
I was popular,

32:54.562 --> 32:59.116
but I had no idea who I was
or what I wanted.

32:59.200 --> 33:02.035
And I started
a clothing line,

33:02.103 --> 33:04.821
and it became more successful
than I could have ever dreamed.

33:04.906 --> 33:07.824
But even at the height
of my success,

33:07.909 --> 33:10.294
I always felt
like something was missing.

33:10.378 --> 33:13.046
♪ I believe I,
I believe I ♪

33:13.114 --> 33:15.666
Love. A family.

33:15.750 --> 33:19.285
And then I met Julian.

33:19.337 --> 33:21.621
And he is
an amazing director,

33:21.673 --> 33:24.124
but he's
an even more amazing man,

33:24.175 --> 33:27.728
and I know that he's gonna be
the most amazing father.

33:27.795 --> 33:30.013
So there was a time

33:30.098 --> 33:33.767
when I didn't know who I was
or who I wanted to be.

33:33.818 --> 33:37.187
But I've known
for a long time now.

33:37.271 --> 33:39.156
I want to be a mom.

33:39.240 --> 33:42.442
And I want to see
Julian be a dad.

33:42.493 --> 33:47.497
And I want our child
to feel loved and protected,

33:47.582 --> 33:50.150
even when
they're struggling,

33:50.201 --> 33:54.171
like I did,
like -- like we all have.

33:54.255 --> 33:58.792
♪ With our hands
only tied together ♪

33:58.843 --> 34:00.677
You look
really wasted here.

34:00.762 --> 34:02.629
I was.

34:02.680 --> 34:04.715
I have better ones if --

34:04.799 --> 34:08.518
no, it's -- it's okay.

34:08.603 --> 34:11.221
Thank you
for telling me the truth.

34:13.440 --> 34:15.225
I'll think about it,
okay?

34:15.309 --> 34:19.012
♪ You know
that I'm in love with you ♪

34:19.063 --> 34:23.065
♪ yeah, you know
that I'm in love with you ♪

34:23.150 --> 34:27.821
♪ yeah, you know
that I'm in love with you ♪

34:45.670 --> 34:48.255
You can't have an open bottle
on the mound in the pros.

34:50.085 --> 34:51.469
Think you got to pour it
in a cup.

34:53.422 --> 34:55.422
You know how you spent the day
today with your kid,

34:55.475 --> 34:58.326
just all the coaching
and tryouts?

35:00.763 --> 35:04.566
To this day, my dad's
come to one game --

35:04.617 --> 35:07.536
one.

35:07.603 --> 35:10.438
And I pitched right here
on campus.

35:12.959 --> 35:15.894
I'm sorry, man.
That's crazy.

35:15.962 --> 35:17.162
It's okay, though,

35:17.246 --> 35:19.915
'cause this is the only place
in the world

35:19.982 --> 35:21.833
that he can't get to me --

35:21.918 --> 35:23.668
right here on this mound.

35:29.458 --> 35:32.794
I guess
he doesn't understand it.

35:32.845 --> 35:35.180
But you want
to know a secret?

35:35.264 --> 35:37.432
Neither do I.

35:37.483 --> 35:39.467
And I don't want to know.

35:40.970 --> 35:44.489
I throw the ball,
they swing, they miss.

35:44.574 --> 35:47.475
I don't want
to know why or how.

35:47.527 --> 35:51.980
There's kind of a -- a beauty
in that, you know?

35:52.081 --> 35:54.533
Yeah, I do know.

35:54.617 --> 35:56.535
Which part?

35:56.619 --> 35:57.869
All of it.

35:59.154 --> 36:01.756
So you guys want to do this,
be my agents?

36:01.824 --> 36:03.658
We do.

36:03.709 --> 36:05.159
But I got to warn you,

36:05.211 --> 36:07.662
it might upset your father
a little bit.

36:07.713 --> 36:08.830
You okay with that?

36:13.936 --> 36:15.303
Perfect.

36:17.974 --> 36:19.608
Welcome to Fortitude.

36:23.229 --> 36:26.347
I'm home.

36:26.399 --> 36:28.116
What is all this?

36:28.183 --> 36:29.801
I wrote a couple stories
for you.

36:29.869 --> 36:31.853
I-I thought
it might help.

36:31.904 --> 36:34.573
And I set up the camera so we
can practice them together.

36:37.359 --> 36:40.579
When I went on the air
for the first time,

36:40.630 --> 36:44.416
someone I love
gave me this great advice --

36:44.500 --> 36:46.134
just pretend
you're talking to me.

36:46.201 --> 36:48.086
Someone you love.

36:48.170 --> 36:49.704
Yeah.

36:55.595 --> 36:57.211
Best roommate ever.

36:57.263 --> 36:58.563
You ready?

37:00.733 --> 37:03.068
♪ Good night, big moon ♪

37:03.152 --> 37:05.570
♪ sweet dreams, baby ♪

37:05.655 --> 37:09.074
♪ if I could have one wish
tonight ♪

37:10.943 --> 37:13.394
Well, that doesn't sound
that bad.

37:13.446 --> 37:14.529
It <i>was</i> that bad.

37:14.580 --> 37:15.897
There's no possible way

37:15.948 --> 37:18.199
she wants us as the parents
after today.

37:18.251 --> 37:20.702
Millie basically told her
that we're destitute

37:20.753 --> 37:22.921
while joking
about her drug problem,

37:23.005 --> 37:25.757
and then my mother showed up
yelling about prison.

37:25.841 --> 37:28.093
Hey, look...

37:28.177 --> 37:30.078
I'm sure
we can explain it.

37:30.129 --> 37:31.963
I tried that.

37:32.048 --> 37:34.132
She still left.

37:34.216 --> 37:37.135
♪ Your heart will break and ♪

37:37.219 --> 37:41.273
♪ you swear that
all your strength is gone ♪

37:41.357 --> 37:47.095
♪ but then you'll find a way
to carry on ♪

37:47.146 --> 37:48.647
Hey.

37:48.731 --> 37:49.814
Hey!

37:49.899 --> 37:51.316
Oh, come here.

37:51.400 --> 37:53.101
Mm.

37:53.152 --> 37:54.435
Oh.
What was that for?

37:54.487 --> 37:56.104
That was because Jamie said
he had a great day,

37:56.155 --> 37:58.239
and his dad
was a big part of that.

37:58.291 --> 37:59.874
Well,
how was his mom's day?

37:59.942 --> 38:02.327
It was good.
It was great, actually.

38:02.411 --> 38:06.281
Um, and I think Lydia
really enjoyed it, too.

38:06.349 --> 38:07.332
Lydia.

38:07.416 --> 38:08.800
Yeah.

38:08.884 --> 38:11.803
I didn't want to get my hopes up
until I talked to Quinn,

38:11.887 --> 38:13.738
but what do you think?

38:13.806 --> 38:17.291
Nathan, Haley, Jamie,
and Lydia.

38:17.343 --> 38:18.677
It's perfect.

38:18.761 --> 38:20.979
Yeah?
Mm-hmm.

38:22.464 --> 38:24.099
Mm.

38:24.150 --> 38:26.568
♪ So don't be scared when ♪

38:26.635 --> 38:29.437
♪ you're in the darkness ♪

38:29.488 --> 38:32.524
So, was it good,
the shower?

38:32.608 --> 38:34.776
Huh? Yeah.

38:34.827 --> 38:36.911
♪ You think it's gone but... ♪

38:36.979 --> 38:39.914
Hey. Where's your head,
Quinn James?

38:39.982 --> 38:44.369
Just thinking about something
the girls said today.

38:44.453 --> 38:48.823
♪ Even when it's lost,
it can be found ♪

38:48.874 --> 38:51.176
Wait.

38:51.260 --> 38:53.161
Pull over.

38:53.212 --> 38:58.550
♪ Heaven knows
that it's a crazy ride ♪

38:58.634 --> 39:03.171
♪ it's never perfect
all the time ♪

39:03.222 --> 39:06.841
Hey, look at you!
That looks awesome!

39:06.892 --> 39:08.276
High five.

39:08.343 --> 39:09.944
Ha-ha.

39:10.012 --> 39:12.346
Thanks.
Did you have fun at your party?

39:12.398 --> 39:14.399
I did.
I missed you, though.

39:14.483 --> 39:16.534
And I think
the baby did, too.

39:16.619 --> 39:19.070
Yeah, dad said you were gonna
name her after grandma.

39:19.138 --> 39:20.572
Mm-hmm.
I think that's pretty cool.

39:20.656 --> 39:22.574
I made her a present.

39:22.658 --> 39:24.159
You did?

39:24.210 --> 39:25.359
"To Lydia.

39:25.411 --> 39:27.746
"I can't wait
to play catch with you.

39:27.813 --> 39:29.714
Love,
your big brother Jamie."

39:29.799 --> 39:31.166
She's gonna love it.

39:31.217 --> 39:33.968
And she's gonna love having you
as a big brother.

39:35.471 --> 39:36.888
Come here.

39:36.972 --> 39:41.593
♪ Heaven knows
that it's a crazy ride ♪

39:41.677 --> 39:42.844
Quinn?

39:42.895 --> 39:44.179
There's something
about this place.

39:44.230 --> 39:48.066
It feels so familiar.

39:48.150 --> 39:49.768
Do you feel it?

39:49.852 --> 39:53.188
♪ ...Crazy ride ♪

39:53.239 --> 39:54.739
Beautiful.

39:54.824 --> 39:56.024
I was gonna
take you here.

39:56.075 --> 39:59.160
Yeah.

39:59.228 --> 40:01.329
Have we been here before?

40:01.397 --> 40:03.665
Promise me that you'll
go back here someday.

40:03.732 --> 40:05.566
We'll go together.

40:05.618 --> 40:08.903
No.

40:08.954 --> 40:11.506
I just want you to know
that I love you.

40:11.573 --> 40:13.792
And I love us
just where we are.

40:13.876 --> 40:15.960
You're perfect with me.

40:16.045 --> 40:17.378
I love us, too.

40:17.430 --> 40:20.849
And just where we are
is my favorite place to be.

40:26.755 --> 40:31.192
♪ Heaven knows
that it's a crazy ride ♪

40:32.761 --> 40:34.896
♪ It's never perfect
all the time ♪

40:34.947 --> 40:37.282
Oh, hey, Chloe.
Hi.

40:37.366 --> 40:38.450
Is Brooke here?

40:38.534 --> 40:39.651
I need to tell you guys
something.

40:39.735 --> 40:40.785
Yeah.

40:40.870 --> 40:43.154
Yeah. Hi, Chloe.
I'm here.

40:43.239 --> 40:44.489
Hi.

40:44.573 --> 40:47.475
Um, so, I've -- I've thought
a lot about today

40:47.543 --> 40:49.828
and about everything,
really.

40:49.912 --> 40:54.332
And, uh, it seems like you guys
have a lot of baggage.

40:54.416 --> 40:55.884
♪ Baby, hold on tight ♪

40:55.951 --> 40:58.119
The thing is,
I-I want two people

40:58.170 --> 41:01.956
who are gonna love this baby,
who can care for this baby,

41:02.007 --> 41:06.728
and who will understand
when they make a mistake.

41:06.795 --> 41:09.797
So I think it's okay
that you guys have, too.

41:11.800 --> 41:15.653
And that's the reason why I want
you guys to be the parents.

41:21.610 --> 41:23.912
♪ Good night, big moon ♪

41:23.979 --> 41:28.783
♪ sweet dreams, baby ♪

